Path: godot/tutorials/shaders/shader_reference/particle_shader.rst
Summary: Describes the available render modes for particle shaders.

Render modes:
* keep_data (Description: Do not clear previous data on restart.)
* disable_force (Description: Disable attractor force.)
* disable_velocity (Description: Ignore VELOCITY value.)
* collision_use_scale (Description: Scale the particle's size for collisions.)
---CHUNK---
Document: Shader Reference
Path: godot/tutorials/shaders/shader_reference/particle_shader.rst
Summary: Explains the meaning of 'in', 'out', and 'inout' qualifiers for built-in shader variables.
'in' values are read-only. 'out' values can be written to but may not contain sensible defaults. 'inout' values have sensible defaults and can be written to. Samplers are read-only and not marked.
